I rarely leave reviews but I definitely need to shout out the Trufa Restaurant!!!! Say What?!?! 1. Amazing service and very kind! It was last minute and we traveled all the way from Jersey for a great meal. Yes I understand it’s Covid but I just needed something different. At the very late minute, this staff was able to accommodate my cousin and I at nearly closing time!!!! HOW FREAKING SPECIAL DURING THE COVID? They made us feel very special. I ordered everything I wanted. Fried calamari, chicken Caesar salad, spring rolls, Alfredo with shrimp and chicken. The bread was offered and it was made fresh from the small restaurant. I adore little features where you can see the chefs prepare your meals. Yes. Small but friendly. Cozy. A touch of love. Soft music. Sweet desserts.  As I write this review, I am finishing my salad and remembering how worth it was to visit the Trufa! Thanks again for the experience and I look forward to my return.

We walked in after hunger had hit us and we were hard-pressed to find something in the neighborhood at reasonable prices, vegetarian-friendly, AND healthy - didn't involve dollops of cheese.  It's an unassuming place with an interesting ambience and a kitchen that is not closed off. It's like being at a food festival where the cooking area with the grills and chefs are all directly in front of you, but there is also exclusive closed seating space covered with brick and mortar. While this struck us as odd when we first got in, it grew on us over the course of the lovely meal.  The service is extremely friendly and prompt. What stunned not just us, but all our neighbors (at tables all around, that allows a maximum seating of about 15 people tops) is the portion size. The portion sizes are unexpectedly huge, making the prices completely reasonable. The food is SO fresh. The ingredients look farm-to-table. Even the fries are so fresh and light. You don't feel your arteries clogging up as you chow them down. We got the vegetarian panini and the caprese salad. Among the best that we've had - both of them! The mozzarella, I gotta say, was so fresh and yummy.  Over the hour or two that we were there, we could see several regulars being recognized by face and picking up food that was already waiting for them. Not surprised! It's that kinda place.  The experience left us with a happy food-high that led to a comatose stroll all around the neighborhood, transforming a chore-day-saturday into a happy, healthy evening.

Don't get the Blue Sangria! You've been warned!  Toxic drink aside, the food is good. One of the first "classier" restaurants to come to HH. The lamb was surprisingly delicious, cutting the bitterness of the blue sangria I will forever try to forget. The burgers are HUGE and hearty. The fries (at least in the restaurant) are crispy and fresh which has been improved since my first try.  Most memorable experience was ordering a chicken basil sandwich to split with a friend and they so kindly brought us two separate plates with our halves as well as a generous side of fries. Honestly, not many restaurants would be that nice.  Great service, good food!

Fantastic local restaurant.  Serving riffs off of Italian/American cuisine. The restaurant is small, with around 6 tables only. The food is great.  Lovely pasta.  Nice daily specials.  Sandwiches are very good.  The burgers are excellent.  At the restaurant, service can be a bit of a hit or miss.  The manager is hardly there and the young man often stationed as the waiter-cum-supervisor would probably rather be hanging out at a lower-east side club than doing his job.  That said, the delivery is good and a god-send to this neighborhood, which for years has been a dry desert of good food.

The is the lil' restaurant that could! They have a good selection of items with a lot of vegetarian and healthy options. They have decent wines and I definitely recommend their sangria. In short, if you haven't tried Trufa out yet, you're definitely missing out on a real gem.

So this was the first place I had ever gone to when I first moved to the neighborhood - and I mean the very same night I moved, before even unpacking. The scenario is this: I had just finished packing and moving within one LONG day with the help of my amazing girlfriend and we were famished. Being vegan we immediately searched around for vegan options. Score! Trufa offers a portobello burger that's vegan if you get it on multigrain bread (delicious) and without the pesto (has parmesan). The burger was a hit! Huge, cruelty-free meaty flavors mashed well with the condiments and hefty-sized artisan multigrain bun. The fries it came with also tasted fresh. The sangria would get a review all of it's own if that were even possible, but suffice it to say: you need everything they serve, in yo' mouf... Like now. What are you waiting for?
